<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1942,2003]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="314" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
This tribe is diverse and numerous in tropical and subtropical regions worldwide. 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1226,1942,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Epilachnini">Epilachnini</taxonomicName>
are phytophagous ladybugs. Taxonomy of this tribe is complex and controversial. There is still debate between authors on the validity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Li, 1961" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="1961" box="[184,477,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Henosepilachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[184,366,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Henosepilachna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[377,477,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" refString="Li, C. S. &amp; Cook, E. F. (1961) The Epilachninae of Taiwan (Col.: Coccinellidae). Pacific Insects, Honolulu, 3, 31 - 91." type="journal article" year="1961">
Li, 
<number box="[419,477,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and its possible synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat" authorityName="Chevrolat" box="[868,1105,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Epilachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[868,983,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Epilachna</emphasis>
Chevrolat
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1115,1137,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">in</emphasis>
Dejean, 
<number box="[1244,1303,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="1836.0">1836</number>
. But recent molecular phylogenetic analysis of 
<taxonomicName box="[562,691,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Epilachnini">Epilachnini</taxonomicName>
from both genera confirmed that they belong to distinct groups (
<bibRefCitation author="Kobayashi" box="[158,419,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" refString="Kobayashi, N., Ohta, Y., Katoh, T., Kahono, S., Hartini, S. &amp; Katakura, H. (2009) Molecular phylogenetic analysis of three groups of Asian epilachnine ladybird beetles recognized by the female internal reproductive organs and modes of sperm transfer. Journal of Natural History, 43, 1637 - 1649." type="journal article" year="2009">
Kobayashi 
<emphasis box="[290,350,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[360,419,224,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Szawaryn" box="[435,687,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" refString="Szawaryn, K., Bocak, L., Slipinski, A., Escalona, H. E. &amp; Tomaszewska, W. (2015) Phylogeny and evolution of phytophagous ladybird beetles (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae: Epilachnini), with recognition of new genera. Systematic Entomology, 40, 547 - 569." type="journal article" year="2015">
Szawaryn 
<emphasis box="[556,615,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[626,687,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="2015.0">2015</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Our present note does not intend to resolve this nomenclatural question. So we follow the nomenclatural decisions of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bielawski" box="[766,960,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" refString="Bielawski, R. (1972) The Epilachninae (Coleoptera, Coccinellidae) of New Caledonia. Bulletin de l'Academie polonaise des sciences. Serie des sciences biologiques, 20, 557 - 561." type="journal article" year="1972">
Bielawski (
<number box="[893,951,260,284]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="1972.0">1972</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
regarding New Caledonian 
<taxonomicName box="[1276,1409,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Epilachnini">Epilachnini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
